A security firm Hogan Guards has been awarded Africa’s most trusted risk management solutions company of the decade at the African Quality Achievement Awards (AQAA) and  the Africa’s Quality Congress at Sheraton Hotel , Ikeja, Lagos. The firm was selected by experts from across Africa, including South Africa, Uganda, Ghana, Liberia and Nigeria.   NIMASA, Navy renew fight against piracy, oil theft     Minister seeks more investments in economic zones     African start-up joins Mastercard programme   Indigenous organisations as well as foreign and multinational companies in Africa were also honoured. Hogan Guards Chief Executive Officer, Mr. Paul Ibirogba said: “We are truly honoured to be recognised as a continental leader in our industry. This award would not be possible without the thousands of committed workers in our organisation.” He praised the company’s personnel and their professionalism in mitigating terrorism, armed robbery and fire outbreaks.